column5: 14 of 20 here. Not likely to try again. I believe the "quit when your ahead" theory. Not likely to do any better.
An honest 18 /20 But I have had most of the bait fish types in an aquaruim at one time or another.  If I had my native species of Ontario book with me I could have cheated!  jjcanoe

Just tried the test again 3 times - scored 17/20, 15/20 and 19/20.  I knew there was a reason for catching all those small fish (chubs, shiners and minnows) during the year!  Taking the test is a good way of learning about a few unusual species.  007
Easy 19/20 first try! lol i've studied fish recently in one of my classes
I don't think i got one minnow right. I rarely use them anyways but still. 11/20
so far I get the first half of the question right every time but the second half who know..it's a shiner, I really don't care about the fine points
15/20 here... darn those tiny little buggers! HH
11/20....ha, half those fish i have never seen before

Havent seen this posted here before. I came across it surfing around and found it interesting. I apologize if its been on here in the past.  http://fishiqtest.com  I only scored 12 out of 20. I guess it's a passing grade lol .
I sucked, 11/20.  Always had trouble with types of minnows.  But I did get the one right I use almost exclusively!
16 / 20 - guess I could'a done worse!  Don
WOW...thats harder than i thought !!!!...everyone should take this,well at least im not totally stupid i got 15/20,thanks for posting!!!! go ahead everyone take it its cool....cheers

haha
12/20 for me but at least I know what a Pickeral isn't!

....'Sigh' 11/20.......I don't know nuttin'  Brian, I never got the pickeral question on my test........there must be different tests available. I thought they all looked like minnows sorta....hahaha Loved the Stickleback Q........it just had to be and then the 2nd portion of the same Q asked, Ninespine or threespine........best Q...all you had to do was count the spines....Duh!  Thanks for posting the test.......a nice time waster.

I got 11/20. Interesting about all the baitfish. Wonder if that has anything to do with the commercial ban and limit of angler caught baitfish. Maybe they are going to try and educate anglers about catching baitfish, identifying them in an effort not to transport non-native species.
At least I got the carp right!
